					<item>
				<guid>http://www.scpwiki.com/forum/t-1036568#post-2296061</guid>
				<title>(no title)</title>
				<link>http://www.scpwiki.com/forum/t-1036568/activity-documentation-file-11-a#post-2296061</link>
				<description></description>
				<pubDate>Sat, 16 May 2015 03:47:13 +0000</pubDate>
				<wikidot:authorName>Communism will win</wikidot:authorName>				<wikidot:authorUserId>617958</wikidot:authorUserId>				<content:encoded>
					<![CDATA[
						 <blockquote> <p>The Oneiroi gardens, they call it. Or that's what my Master called it. I didn't call it anything, because it was before I was with the written word. That was when I was free.</p> </blockquote> <p>I take it this a reference to the Serpent's Hand &#8212; first in the reference to a garden, <a href="http://www.scpwiki.com/incident-report-x23">which is the Serpent's place</a>, and the reference to the written word reminds me of <a href="http://www.scpwiki.com/the-tale-of-the-library">The Tale of the Library</a>, with which the Hand is closely associated. That might just be me, though.</p> <blockquote> <p><em><strong>theymightbegiants</strong>letmegrowawakethenighttimedream</em></p> </blockquote> <p>And that's when I realized that Roget wrote this.</p> <blockquote> <p>If what you say is true, the dream harvesters could be dangerous.</p> </blockquote> <p><a href="https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=uLSefwsluR0">I lol'd</a>.</p> <p>Enjoyed the references, well-written all-around, upvoted.</p> 
				 	]]>
				</content:encoded>							</item>
